# ESP32 Zigbee Lidar Distance Sensor — User Guide
## Version 1.9 OTA

---

## Overview

This ESP32-C6 device pairs a VL53L1X Time-of-Flight distance sensor with Zigbee connectivity for home automation. It reports both a smoothed (EMA-filtered) and raw distance value to Hubitat simultaneously, supports OTA firmware updates, and includes a built-in web server for configuration — available whenever the device is in WiFi mode.

**Key Features:**
- Zigbee distance reporting to Hubitat via two endpoints: EMA-smoothed (ep10) and raw (ep11)
- Mutually exclusive radio modes — WiFi and Zigbee never run at the same time, eliminating radio interference
- Three operating modes: Zigbee-only (normal), WiFi-only, and OTA update
- OTA firmware updates via ElegantOTA web interface
- Presence detection with configurable distance threshold
- Stuck-reading watchdog: automatically soft-resets the VL53L1X if the sensor hangs on an implausible repeated value
- Per-device friendly name via lookup table in the .ino file
- Factory reset via BOOT button hold (EQP) or Side Button long-press (Nesso N1)

---

## Radio Architecture

The ESP32-C6 cannot reliably run WiFi and Zigbee simultaneously. The device enforces strict mutual exclusivity:

| Mode | Zigbee | WiFi | Purpose |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| **Zigbee-only** (normal) | ✅ ON | ❌ OFF | Distance reporting to Hubitat |
| **WiFi-only** | ❌ OFF | ✅ ON | Web control panel + OTA access |
| **OTA mode** | ❌ OFF | ✅ ON | Firmware update only |

The device always boots into **Zigbee-only mode** unless a flag has been set to request WiFi-only mode or OTA mode.

