## Operating Modes

### Zigbee-Only Mode (Normal Operation)

This is the default mode. The device:
- Reads the VL53L1X sensor every 10 seconds
- Reports both smoothed and raw distance to Hubitat via two Zigbee endpoints
- Monitors Zigbee connection; reboots to rejoin if disconnected for more than 5 minutes
- Keeps WiFi radio OFF

**How to exit:** Use the Hubitat "Enable WiFi Mode" command button to switch to WiFi-only mode, or use the power-cycle OTA trick to enter OTA mode.

---

### WiFi-Only Mode

Entered when Hubitat sends the "Enable WiFi Mode" command (or when the device reboots with the `wifiRequested` flag set). Zigbee is never started. WiFi connects at full power.

The device will retry WiFi connection up to 3 times (30 seconds each) before giving up and rebooting back to Zigbee mode.

**Web control panel** is available at `http://[DEVICE_IP]/` and shows device status plus action buttons.

**Timeout:** After 15 minutes in WiFi-only mode, the device automatically reboots back to Zigbee mode.

**How to exit:** Click the **Return to Zigbee Mode** button on the web control panel, or wait for the 15-minute timeout.

---

### OTA Mode

Entered via the power-cycle trigger (see below), via the `/ota-mode` endpoint while in WiFi-only mode, or via Front Button long-press (Nesso N1 only). Zigbee is never started. The ElegantOTA upload interface is available at `http://[DEVICE_IP]/update`.

**LED indicator:** SOS pattern (· · · — — — · · ·) flashes continuously while OTA mode is active.

**Display indicator (Nesso N1 only):** The display shows the upload URL (`http://[IP]/update`) with "Zigbee OFF" in the footer. During the 15-second OTA entry window immediately after Zigbee starts, the display instead flashes alternating red and black backgrounds with the message "Unplug now to enter OTA mode" and a countdown.

**Timeout:** After 15 minutes with no upload, the device reboots back to Zigbee mode.

**How to exit:** Upload firmware (device reboots automatically), click **Return to Zigbee Mode** on the web page, or wait for the 15-minute timeout.

**Exit via button (Nesso N1 only):** While in OTA mode, hold the **Front Button for 3 seconds** to return immediately to Zigbee mode. A 0.5-second hold shows a confirmation prompt on the display; releasing before 3 seconds cancels.

