## Distance Reporting

The device always reports both values on every valid sensor reading:

| Endpoint | Description | Zigbee Cluster |
|----------|-------------|---------------|
| **ep10** | EMA-smoothed distance | Illuminance (0x0400) |
| **ep11** | Raw (unsmoothed) distance | Illuminance (0x0400) |

**EMA Smoothing** (Exponential Moving Average, alpha = 0.6) runs continuously on ep10. It reduces sensor noise and produces stable values for dashboards and automations, while ep11 provides the instantaneous reading for applications that need faster response.

**Report interval:** The sensor reads every 10 seconds by default (`SENSOR_READ_INTERVAL_MS`). The Hubitat driver's Minimum Report Interval setting throttles how often the Zigbee stack forwards reports to the hub — if set higher than 10 seconds, Hubitat receives reports at the driver's configured interval. Report Delta (minimum mm change) also controls when a report is sent.

