## Device Naming

Each physical device can be given a friendly name by adding its chip ID to the `deviceMappings[]` table in the .ino file:

```cpp
const DeviceMapping deviceMappings[] = {
  { 0x70A95AFEFFCA4C40ULL, "South Car Bay LIDAR" },
  { 0x6C355AFEFFCA4C40ULL, "North Car Bay LIDAR" },
};
```

The device name appears in the Serial Monitor banner, the web control panel, and the Hubitat driver page. If a chip ID is not in the table, the device uses a default name of `LIDAR-` followed by the last 4 hex digits of the chip ID.

