## LED and Display Status Indicators

| Pattern | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| Fast blinking (300ms) | Zigbee not connected — searching or pairing |
| Solid on | Zigbee connected and reporting normally |
| SOS (· · · — — — · · ·) | OTA entry window open (15s after Zigbee starts — unplug now to trigger OTA on next boot) **or** OTA mode active — connect to `/update` to upload firmware |

Both the OTA entry window and OTA mode use the same SOS LED pattern. The Nesso N1 display distinguishes between them (see below).

**Nesso N1 display indicators (in addition to LED):**

| Display | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| Flashing red/black background with countdown | OTA entry window open (15s) — unplug now to trigger OTA mode on next boot |
| "OTA Update Mode" with URL and "Zigbee OFF" footer | OTA mode active — upload firmware at the shown URL |
| Normal distance screen | Zigbee-only mode, operating normally |

**Nesso N1 display modes (cycle via Front Button short press):**

| Mode | Display |
|------|---------|
| 0 | Normal layout: header bar, smoothed distance (green), raw distance (yellow), footer with connection status and good/bad read counts |
| 1 | Full-screen: smoothed distance only (green, large font) |
| 2 | Full-screen: raw distance only (yellow, large font) |
| 3 | Full-screen: alternates between smoothed (green) and raw (yellow) every 10 seconds *(default)* |

