## Entering OTA Mode

### Method 1: Power-Cycle Trigger (No Hubitat required)

Use this when you need to update firmware without Hubitat access.

1. **Plug in** — device boots and Zigbee starts
2. **Watch for the SOS LED pattern** (· · · — — — · · ·) — this signals the 15-second OTA window is open
3. **Unplug within 15 seconds** of seeing the SOS pattern
4. **Plug in again** — device detects the flag and enters OTA mode (LED continues SOS)
5. Navigate to `http://[DEVICE_IP]/update` to upload firmware

> **Note:** If you don't unplug within 15 seconds, the flag clears automatically and normal power interruptions are safe. Simply plug in again and repeat from step 1.

### Method 2: Via Hubitat + WiFi-Only Mode

1. In Hubitat, click **Enable WiFi Mode** on the device page
2. Device reboots into WiFi-only mode and connects to WiFi
3. Navigate to `http://[DEVICE_IP]/` for the control panel
4. Click **Upload OTA Firmware** (goes directly to `/update`) or click **Enter OTA Mode** to reboot into dedicated OTA mode
5. Upload your `.bin` firmware file

### Method 3: Via the `/ota-mode` Endpoint (while in WiFi-only mode)

Navigate to `http://[DEVICE_IP]/ota-mode` — the device will reboot into OTA mode.

### Method 4: Front Button Long-Press (Nesso N1 only)

While in normal Zigbee mode, hold the **Front Button for 3 seconds**. A 0.5-second hold shows a confirmation prompt; releasing early cancels. On confirmation the device saves a `directOTA` flag (which survives software resets) and reboots into OTA mode.

