## Web Control Panel

The web interface is available in **WiFi-only mode** and **OTA mode**. Navigate to `http://[DEVICE_IP]/` to see the status page.

### Status Page (`/`)

All modes show a status table with:
- Device Name
- Current mode (Zigbee-Only / WiFi-Only / OTA Update Mode)
- Zigbee connection state (Zigbee-only mode only)
- IP address, WiFi RSSI (colour-coded: green ≥ −70 dBm, amber ≥ −80, red < −80), channel, and MAC address
- A warning banner if signal is too weak for a reliable OTA upload

### WiFi-Only Mode Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `/` | GET | Status page + action buttons |
| `/update` | GET | ElegantOTA firmware upload interface |
| `/reboot-wifi` | ANY | Reboot WiFi connection (stays in WiFi-only mode) |
| `/zigbee-mode` | ANY | Return to Zigbee mode (reboots) |
| `/ota-mode` | POST/GET | Reboot into OTA mode |

### OTA Mode Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `/` | GET | Status page + Upload button |
| `/update` | GET | ElegantOTA firmware upload interface |
| `/reboot-wifi` | ANY | Reboot WiFi connection (stays in OTA mode) |
| `/zigbee-mode` | ANY | Return to Zigbee mode (reboots) |

