## Hubitat Driver (v1.26)

### Current State Attributes

| Attribute | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `(01) Millimeters` | Smoothed distance in mm (ep10) |
| `(02) Centimeters` | Smoothed distance in cm |
| `(03) Meters` | Smoothed distance in m |
| `(04) Inches` | Smoothed distance in inches |
| `(05) Feet` | Smoothed distance in feet |
| `(06) Yards` | Smoothed distance in yards |
| `(07) Raw Millimeters` | Raw (unsmoothed) distance in mm (ep11) |
| `(08) Raw Centimeters*` | Raw distance in cm |
| `(09) Raw Meters*` | Raw distance in m |
| `(10) Raw Inches*` | Raw distance in inches |
| `(11) Raw Feet*` | Raw distance in feet |
| `(12) Raw Yards*` | Raw distance in yards |
| `Selected Display` | Distance in the unit chosen in preferences |
| `presence` | `"present"` or `"not present"` based on threshold |
| `firmwareVersion` | Firmware version string from device (e.g. `1.9 EQP OTA`) |
| `Distance Summary` | All smoothed units in one string (mm \| cm \| m \| in \| ft \| yd) |
| `Raw Summary` | All raw units in one string (mm \| cm \| m \| in \| ft \| yd) |
| `healthStatus` | `"online"` or `"offline"` based on Zigbee message activity |
| `lastCheckin` | Timestamp of the most recent Zigbee message received |

> **\*** Shown only if "Publish raw converted unit attributes ... as separate events" is enabled

### Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `enableWiFiMode` | Sends On command to ep12 — device saves flag and reboots into WiFi-only mode |
| `refresh` | Reads current distance from ep10 |
| `setPresenceThreshold(mm)` | Sets the distance threshold for presence detection |

### Driver Preferences

| Preference | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| Display Units | mm | Unit shown in `Selected Display` attribute |
| Presence Detection Threshold | 1500 mm | Distance below this = `"present"` |
| Minimum Report Interval | 5 sec | Zigbee stack minimum time between reports |
| Maximum Report Interval | 300 sec | Zigbee stack maximum silence before forced report |
| Report Delta | 50 mm | Minimum change to trigger a report |
| Publish Raw Converted Attributes | false | When enabled, also sends separate events for raw cm/m/in/ft/yd; when disabled, these still appear in Raw Summary but are not individual events |
| Health Timeout | 30 min | Mark device offline if no Zigbee messages received within this window |
| Enable debug logging | true | Logs raw Zigbee messages to Hubitat log |

> **Report Interval notes:** The sketch reads the sensor every 10 seconds. Setting Minimum Report Interval below 10 seconds has no additional effect. Maximum Report Interval ensures Hubitat receives a heartbeat even when the reading is stable. After changing preferences, click **Save Preferences** to push the new reporting config to the device.

### Pairing / Re-Pairing

The driver fingerprint matches on `manufacturer: "Espressif"` (EQP board) or `manufacturer: "Arduino"` (Nesso N1 board) — there is no `model:` field in the fingerprint. The model string (e.g. `LIDAR_Sensor_v1.9 EQP OTA`) is separately read from the Basic cluster attribute 0x0005 during `configure()` and decoded into the `firmwareVersion` attribute. If you add a new endpoint (e.g. during sketch development), a factory reset and re-pair is required to register the new endpoint with Hubitat.

